✅ top
Shows real-time system performance like CPU, memory usage, running processes, etc.
Used to monitor and manage system resources.
Syntax: top

✅ df
Displays disk space usage of file systems in Linux.
Command: df -h shows size in human-readable format.
Syntax: df

✅ iostat
Reports CPU stats and input/output stats for devices.
Used to monitor system I/O performance.
Syntax: iostat

✅ shutdown
Used to turn off or restart the system safely.
Example: shutdown -h now shuts down immediately.
Syntax: 
shutdown -h now   # Shuts down the system immediately
shutdown -r now   # Reboots the system immediately

